snippet.textDisplay: @Jenns Property Unfortunately, people like Davidson fill a need that many have to "know more" than everyone around them.  They will latch onto whomever is pushing an idea they can get behind.  Looking at Davidson's words used in videos and responses, it seems when he minored in meteorology he assumed he was going to set the class on it's head with all his "theories".  The professor told him if he ever wanted to succeed in the field he would need to throw all that shit out.  He didn't.  When the sun went quiet to finish it's polarity flip at the same time the IPCC started using cmip6 data sets that allow for better solar forcing modeling he needed a new gimmick to sell.  Catastrophism!  It's all to show his father he's an earner when ya bare bones it ;)
